comment: @note ALL distance units in the fluid box is in meters.

methods.comment: ** Call to get the current added pressure taking into account the pressure toggle. */

The current content measured in Liters

methods.name: GetAvailableSpaceInLiters
methods.comment: The Max content of this Fluid Box Rounded down in Liters

methods.name: AddContentInLiters
methods.comment: Adds a quantity of content supplied in Liters

methods.name: RemoveContentInLiters
methods.comment: Removes a quantity of content, supplied in Liters

methods.name: Reset
methods.comment: Clear the set properties on this box ( Called when flushing a PipeNetwork )

properties.name: Z
properties.comment: The Z mid point for this box. [meters][world space]

properties.name: LowZ
properties.comment: The lowest and highest point on the box. [meters][world space]

properties.name: Height
properties.comment: Height of this box, cannot be 0. [meters]

properties.name: LaminarHeight
properties.comment:
Height from the outflow at which this box can achieve laminar flow. [meters]
Must be in range (0, Height]

properties.name: Content
properties.comment: The current content of this fluid box. [m^3]

properties.name: MaxContent
properties.comment: The max content this fluid box can hold. [m^3]

properties.name: MaxOverfillPct
properties.comment: The maximum overfill allowed in the range (0,1] normalized percent.

properties.name: OVERFILL_USED_FOR_PRESSURE_PCT
properties.comment: This value is in the range (0,1] normalized percent.

properties.name: FlowThrough
properties.comment: Fill and drain is how fast the box is filling up or emptying in [m^3/s].

properties.name: FlowDirection
properties.comment: The flow direction relative to the first component on the pipe, either 1 or -1 if not pipe.

properties.name: FlowLimit
properties.comment: Maximum flow through this box. 0 is unlimited. [m^3/s]

properties.name: PressureColumn
properties.comment: The height of the pressure column at the bottom of this box. [meters]

properties.name: AddedPressure
properties.comment: The added pressure at this point in the simulation, pressure is added to the producer connection. [meters]

properties.name: AddedPressureToggle
properties.comment: Toggle to allow disabling added pressure ( currently used by pumps )

name: UFGFluidIntegrantInterface

comment: Interface for providing consistent access to all properties and components that will be needed to modify and update different aspects of fluid simulation across different buildables

methods.name: GetFluidBox
methods.comment: Returns a pointer the owners fluid box

methods.name: GetPipeConnections
methods.comment: Returns a TArray of pointers to all the owners pipe connections

methods.comment: Notify that the network this fluid integrant belongs to has set its fluid descriptor
